20. Non-goals for v0.1

The following are intentionally out of scope:
	•	nested conditionals
	•	loops
	•	goto
	•	user-defined functions
	•	arbitrary expressions
	•	implicit fuzzy parsing
	•	typo correction in language core
	•	silent fallbacks
	•	hidden defaults that harm reproducibility

⸻

21. Recommended future extensions

These are plausible later additions, but are not part of v0.1:

21.1 Single if/else

A minimal, non-nested conditional form.

21.2 Standardized resource blocks

Reserved sections for checkpoints, loras, vaes, controlnets, encoders, datasets.

21.3 Stronger artifact typing

Explicit artifact classes:
	•	image_set
	•	latent_set
	•	db
	•	video
	•	report
	•	prompt_set

21.4 Canonical realized-CDI export

Official algorithm for reducing a multi-variant CDI into a single realized artifact lineage document.

21.5 Prompt DSL embedding

A formal bridge between Prompt DSL and CDI sections.

⸻

22. Short definition

Beast CDI v0.1 is a strict, line-oriented, linear programming language for defining fully reproducible Beast generators and pipelines.

⸻

23. Proposed motto

Human-readable. Machine-strict. Artifact-complete.

