⸻

Hard truth (important)

Even with everything controlled:
	•	driver updates
	•	minor library changes
	•	hardware differences

can still break determinism.

So you should never promise:

"guaranteed identical outputs everywhere"

Instead:

"guaranteed reproducibility within a defined execution envelope"

